Hossam Badri reveals his final position on the return of the Pyramids players to Egypt
07 Nov 2019, 08:53 by Amr Abou Bakr
Egyptian coach Hossam Badri revealed his position on the exclusion of the seven-team Pyramids team from joining the list of Pharaohs in preparation for the African Nations Cup qualifiers Cameroon 2021. The Egyptian team won against Liberia in a friendly goal by Hamdi Fathi in the match held at Borg El Arab Stadium on Thursday evening. Pyramids decided not to send his players to the national team, objecting. To violate the principle of equality The opportunities after the announcement of the league table, as well as summoning the players at a time outside the international agenda approved by FIFA;
